## Key Patterns and Gotchas

### Determinism (critical — do not break this)
- Use `game.sim.timebase.now_ms()` for ALL timing in sim logic — never `time.time()` or `pygame.time.get_ticks()`
- Use `game.sim.determinism.get_rng("tag")` for ALL randomness — never `random.random()` globals
- Stable ordering for target selection: always tie-break by distance then stable id/index, never raw `set()` iteration

### Hero state machine
- State transitions are driven by `ai/basic_ai.py` (Agent 06's domain)
- Hero movement/physics lives in `hero.update()` in `game/entities/hero.py`
- `hero.can_attack` is the combat gate — set False when inside a building

### Peasant behavior
- Priority order: (1) repair castle, (2) build new buildings, (3) repair other buildings, (4) idle near castle
- Idle behavior: peasants go to offset positions around castle, NOT inside it, unless `castle.is_under_attack`
- `Peasant._spawn_counter` tracks spawn order for deterministic offset slot assignment

### Building construction
- Newly placed buildings: `hp=1`, `is_constructed=False`, `construction_started=False`
- Peasant calls `building.start_construction()` when adjacent (makes it targetable)
- `building.apply_work(dt)` called while peasant is adjacent; construction rate = 10% HP/s

### SkeletonArcher kiting
- Distance band: attack if dist < attack_range; retreat if dist < min_range
- Commitment window: 500ms to avoid oscillation
- Bounded attempts: max 5 kite attempts, then fallback to stand-and-shoot

